  "text": "Bone marrow was isolated from C57BL/6 mice, as has been described [CITATION_1] . Isolated bone marrow cells were differentiated into macrophages in DMEM containing 10% (v/v) heat-inactivated FBS (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Carlsbad, CA, USA), 100 U/ml of penicillin, 100 mg/ml streptomycin, and 20% L929 conditioned medium for 7 d. The adherent cells were used as BMDMs. Cells were maintained at 37°C in a 5% CO 2 /air environment.",
